title: Spending distribution analysis
description: Create a histogram to analyze the distribution of customer spending per visit at a shopping mall, using 'mintcream' for low spenders, 'salmon' for medium spenders, and 'darkcyan' for high spenders.
solution:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

colors = {'Low Spenders': 'mintcream', 'Medium Spenders': 'salmon', 'High Spenders': 'darkcyan'}
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))

for group, color in colors.items():
    plt.hist(df[df['spender_category'] == group]['customer_spend'], bins=20, alpha=0.7, label=group, color=color)
    
plt.title('Distribution of Customer Spending Per Visit at a Shopping Mall')
plt.xlabel('Customer Spending ($)')
plt.ylabel('Frequency')
plt.legend(title='Spender Category')
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()
